SIMPLE: repine
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repine
<hw>Re*pine"</hw> <pr>(r?-p?n")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>pine</ets> to languish.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To fail; to wane.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Reppening</xex> courage yields no foot to foe.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To continue pining; to feel inward discontent which
preys on the spirits; to indulge in envy or complaint; to
murmur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But Lachesis thereat gan to <qex>repine</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What if the head, the eye, or ear <qex>repined</qex>⟦br⟧
To serve mere engines to the ruling mind?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repine
<hw>Re*pine"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Vexation; mortification.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repiner</ent>⟦br⟧
